begin_memory_text: Chit chat about where we are from and the response to COVID-19 in our states. She talked about how the economy is Hawaii is not doing well and that's why she's not going to school or working.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the response to COVID, and red vs. blue state responses to things. She talked about how her dad has gotten more conservative and kind of racist.
end_memory_text: We were talking about her mom and sibling's belief that the end of the world is happening soon and that they will be raptured. Her mom wants to "prove" she is immortal to her when she comes over later. My partner was concerned.
rest_of_day_open: I am looking forward to the rest of my week. I have some time to finish some major projects at work. I have a date tonight with a man that I am interested in and another date tomorrow night. This weekend, I should be able to enjoy the beautiful weather outdoors with my son.
critical_positive: I think we both wanted to get along and have things to talk about. Once we landed on a topic we both had something to say about, the conversation flowed pretty naturally. I think we both wanted to be agreeable and found some common ground to base our conversation on.
critical_negative: Her video was really poor - extremely pixelated - so it was hard for me to see her picture to get a clear idea of who I was talking to or what her facial expressions were. I also interrupted her a few times, and I didn't mean to - I felt bad about that.

begin_memory_text: We talked about basics like where we are from and if we have done the activity before. I also rambled about Australia bushfires because I ramble when I'm nervous
middle_memory_text: In the middle we talked about coronavirus and how it has impacted our locations. We also talked about how the problem is being handled
end_memory_text: At the end we talked about how social media has changed people and i talked about how my family is thinking that the rapture is imminent
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week doesnt really have much structure, I dont have many plans and I dont know what Ill be doing. This is pretty much the norm now, everything is up in the air and its hard to set goals for the short term, let alone the long term
critical_positive: I think my conversation partner and I had quite a few similar perspectives on a variety of subjects, and we had some personal experiences that were similar. I'm glad we both were the type of person that likes to continue a conversation until it ends comfortably rather than stopping at exactly the deadline
critical_negative: It was a little awkward talking about my employment / academic status. I dont have much to talk about or be proud of in these areas so i didnt really know what to say. It was a little embarrassing and made me feel dumb, but it wasnt my conversation partners fault
